40006d04 <CoInvalidateDCacheForV7>:

40006d04:	e92d47f0 	push	{r4, r5, r6, r7, r8, r9, sl, lr}

                BEQ     Finished
40006d14:	0a00001b 	beq	40006d88 <Finished>

                MOV     r10,#0              @/* R10 holds current cache level << 1 */
40006d18:	e3a0a000 	mov	sl, #0

40006d1c <Loop1>:
Loop1:          ADD     r2,r10,r10,LSR #1   @/* R2 holds cache "Set" position */
40006d1c:	e08a20aa 	add	r2, sl, sl, lsr #1
                MOV     r1,r0,LSR r2        @/* Bottom 3 bits are the Cache-type for this level */
40006d20:	e1a01230 	lsr	r1, r0, r2
                AND     r1,R1,#7            @/* Get those 3 bits alone */
40006d24:	e2011007 	and	r1, r1, #7
                CMP     r1,#2
40006d28:	e3510002 	cmp	r1, #2
                BLT     Skip                @/* No cache or only instruction cache at this level */
40006d2c:	ba000012 	blt	40006d7c <Skip>

40006d34:	e3a01000 	mov	r1, #0

40006d38:	ee071f95 	mcr	15, 0, r1, cr7, cr5, {4}
                MRC     p15,1,r1,c0,c0,0    @/* Reads current Cache Size ID register */
40006d3c:	ee301f10 	mrc	15, 1, r1, cr0, cr0, {0}
                AND     r2,r1,#0x7           @/* Extract the line length field */
40006d40:	e2012007 	and	r2, r1, #7
                ADD     r2,r2,#4            @/* Add 4 for the line length offset (log2 16 bytes) */
40006d44:	e2822004 	add	r2, r2, #4
                LDR     r4,=0x3FF
40006d48:	e59f403c 	ldr	r4, [pc, #60]	; 40006d8c <Finished+0x4>
                ANDS    r4,r4,r1,LSR #3     @/* R4 is the max number on the way size (right aligned) */
40006d4c:	e01441a1 	ands	r4, r4, r1, lsr #3
                CLZ     r5,r4               @/* R5 is the bit position of the way size increment */
40006d50:	e16f5f14 	clz	r5, r4
                LDR     r7,=0x00007FFF
40006d54:	e59f7034 	ldr	r7, [pc, #52]	; 40006d90 <Finished+0x8>

40006d58:	e01776a1 	ands	r7, r7, r1, lsr #13

40006d5c <Loop2>:

Loop2:          MOV     r9,r4               @/* R9 working copy of the max way size (right aligned) */
40006d5c:	e1a09004 	mov	r9, r4

40006d60 <Loop3>:
Loop3:          ORR     r11,r10,r9,LSL r5   @/* Factor in the Way number and cache number into R11 */
40006d60:	e18ab519 	orr	fp, sl, r9, lsl r5
                ORR     r11,r11,r7,LSL r2   @/* Factor in the Set number */
40006d64:	e18bb217 	orr	fp, fp, r7, lsl r2
                MCR     p15,0,r11,c7,c14,2  @/* Clean and Invalidate by set/way */
40006d68:	ee07bf5e 	mcr	15, 0, fp, cr7, cr14, {2}
                SUBS    r9,r9,#1            @/* Decrement the Way number */
40006d6c:	e2599001 	subs	r9, r9, #1
                BGE     Loop3
40006d70:	aafffffa 	bge	40006d60 <Loop3>
                SUBS    r7,r7,#1            @/* Decrement the Set number */
40006d74:	e2577001 	subs	r7, r7, #1
                BGE     Loop2
40006d78:	aafffff7 	bge	40006d5c <Loop2>

40006d7c <Skip>:

40006d7c:	e28aa002 	add	sl, sl, #2
                CMP     r3,r10
40006d80:	e153000a 	cmp	r3, sl
                BGT     Loop1
40006d84:	caffffe4 	bgt	40006d1c <Loop1>

40006d88 <Finished>:

40006d88:	e8bd87f0 	pop	{r4, r5, r6, r7, r8, r9, sl, pc}

40006d8c:	000003ff 	strdeq	r0, [r0], -pc	; <UNPREDICTABLE>
